7:["$","article",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-white","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12","children":[["$","header",null,{"className":"mb-8","children":[["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4","children":"5 steps to Manage Wastes according to ISO 14001 EMS"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-4 text-gray-600","children":[["$","time",null,{"dateTime":"2026-01-02T06:31:34+00:00","children":"January 2, 2026"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"inline-block px-3 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 rounded-full text-sm","children":"general"}]]}]]}],null,["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-8 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-blue-500","children":["$","p",null,{"className":"text-gray-700 italic","children":"Waste management is considered as one of the most significant parts while implementing ISO 14001 EMS certification. Read this article further to know how to"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"5 steps to Manage Wastes according to ISO 14001 EMS"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Waste management is considered as one of the most significant parts while implementing ISO 14001 EMS certification as the companies and organization are striving hard for it than accumulating industrial waste and dumping it at a landfill. Manufacturing organizations and units habitually use risky and hazardous materials that when handled without care could cause a threat to human health and therefore to the environment. Such materials are found in everyday things including fluorescent lamps, electronic devices, and certain batteries, as well as in substances like oil and solvents."}],["$","p","2",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"ISO 14001 Environmental Management System certification process will provide a framework and a structured approach to managing waste. While implementing an ISO 14001 EMS standard will help you identify and analyse the environmental aspects. As a result of it, you will be able to determine what wastes are emerging in your processes and with operational controls, you could define how the waste is treated."}],["$","p","3",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"How to manage waste"}],["$","p","4",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"So What is waste management? Waste management is nothing but the method or process of treating industrial wastes, and it offers a wide range of solutions for recycling or reusing those wastes that don’t belong to the garbage. This is often the most sought process by each and every business and business owner around the globe. Waste management disposes of the product and substances that you just have utilized in a secure and economical manner. ISO 14001 doesn’t impose the steps in waste management. However, each company will approach it in line with ISO 14001 EMS needs for the successful acquisition of ISO certification. Check out some common steps in EMS waste management process:"}],["$","p","5",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"1. Evaluate your waste disposal"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"To be able to manage the waste properly, an organization initially has to evaluate whether the waste materials are harmful or not, and also whether managing of that specific waste is regulated by legislation. This step is usually known as classification or categorization of the waste."}],"$L10","$L11","$L12","$L13","$L14","$L15","$L16","$L17","$L18","$L19","$L1a","$L1b","$L1c","$L1d","$L1e","$L1f","$L20","$L21","$L22","$L23","$L24","$L25","$L26","$L27","$L28","$L29","$L2a","$L2b"]}],"$L2c"]}]}]
