e:[["$","title","0",{"children":"Waste Management in line with ISO 14001 | 5 steps to Manage Wastes according to ISO 14001 EMS | Wizms "}],["$","meta","1",{"name":"description","content":"Waste management is considered as one of the most significant parts while implementing ISO 14001 EMS certification. Read this article further to know how to"}],["$","meta","2",{"name":"keywords","content":"5 steps to Manage Wastes according to ISO 14001 EMS"}],["$","meta","3",{"property":"og:title","content":"Waste Management in line with ISO 14001 | 5 steps to Manage Wastes according to ISO 14001 EMS | Wizms "}],["$","meta","4",{"property":"og:description","content":"Waste management is considered as one of the most significant parts while implementing ISO 14001 EMS certification. Read this article further to know how to"}],["$","meta","5",{"property":"og:url","content":"https://wizms.net/waste-management-in-line-with-iso-14001"}],["$","meta","6",{"property":"og:type","content":"article"}],["$","meta","7",{"property":"article:published_time","content":"2026-01-02T06:31:34+00:00"}],["$","meta","8",{"name":"twitter:card","content":"summary"}],["$","meta","9",{"name":"twitter:title","content":"Waste Management in line with ISO 14001 | 5 steps to Manage Wastes according to ISO 14001 EMS | Wizms "}],["$","meta","10",{"name":"twitter:description","content":"Waste management is considered as one of the most significant parts while implementing ISO 14001 EMS certification. Read this article further to know how to"}],["$","link","11",{"rel":"icon","href":"/favicon.ico"}],["$","$L2d","12",{}]]
10:["$","p","7",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"2. Storing the waste"}]
11:["$","p","8",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Depending on the kind of waste, the requirement might vary in terms of storage facilities. Waste could be in both types of states such as solid or liquid form, therefore it is vital to store those wastes accordingly in line with its characteristics. Harmful and dangerous waste should be stored in a very durable, leak-proof instrumentation or container which should be kept intact and closed when not adding or removing waste. Other forms of waste will be needing different types of storage containers. The instrumentation or containers with harmful wastes should be tagged with the words “Hazardous Waste“ and a clear description of the contents along with the date when the waste was initially placed within the containers. Containers should be stored on an impervious surface with enough space to permit for weekly instrumentation inspections."}]
12:["$","p","9",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Additional needs for storing the waste outdoor:"}]
13:["$","p","10",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Managing access to the containers"}]
14:["$","p","11",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Protecting the containers from the weather"}]
15:["$","p","12",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Storing containers of liquid waste on water-resistant surface and container to prevent accidental leaks"}]
16:["$","p","13",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"3. Labelling the waste"}]
17:["$","p","14",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Nonhazardous waste doesn’t have to be compelled to label the waste in any special approach. But this is not the case with hazardous waste. Because harmful waste labelling is commonly prescribed by law and in most countries, an organization should get a license for even generating some forms of dangerous waste. The label for packed harmful and hazardous waste sometimes contains the following information:"}]
18:["$","p","15",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Warning: HAZARDOUS WASTE"}]
19:["$","p","16",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Information regarding the organization who packed the waste: name, address, contact, date of waste packed and name of the person qualified to be answerable for that job. Nature and state of the waste: solid, pastes, sludge, liquids and gaseous substances and powder"}]
1a:["$","p","17",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"4. Regular Disposal of Wastes"}]
1b:["$","p","18",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"An organization is always answerable for its harmful and dangerous industrial wastes. To facilitate this, make sure that these dangerous wastes are being transported and disposed properly at regular intervals, and to cut back your liability. Also, opt for the transporter who fulfils the following requirements:"}]
1c:["$","p","19",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Should have a dangerous waste identification number"}]
1d:["$","p","20",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Should licenced or allowed to transport and dispose dangerous waste"}]
1e:["$","p","21",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Must have fulfilled dangerous waste transportation training necessities"}]
1f:["$","p","22",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Should maintain liability insurance"}]
20:["$","p","23",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Should carry credentials in the vehicle"}]
21:["$","p","24",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Must transports the waste to a premitted dangerous waste facility"}]
22:["$","p","25",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"5. Always have a contingency plan"}]
23:["$","p","26",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Managing and handling dangerous waste is a daunting task and there are high chances for emergency situations which will be caused by mistreatment of the waste or any other cause. So it is recommend to follow the following steps to set up a contingency plan:"}]
24:["$","p","27",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Prevent spill and establish appropriate emergency response and instrumentation in the storage area."}]
25:["$","p","28",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Train workers in line with emergency drill and response procedures that are applicable for your organization."}]
26:["$","p","29",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Establish a strategy to improve performance"}]
27:["$","p","30",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"With the proper support and from environmental and financial perspectives, an effective and efficient waste management system and strategy can completely repay the investment of your time energy and effort you put into it. A proper strategy can incorporate the great degree of flexibility to accommodate changes in raw materials, price differentials, and client expectations."}]
28:["$","p","31",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"You will be ready to demonstrate your waste management strategy to the stakeholders that have following benefits:"}]
29:["$","p","32",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"It can efficiently save money by cutting back material use and waste generation"}]
2a:["$","p","33",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"It will improve your organization's waste management and management of materials"}]
2b:["$","p","34",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"When the strategy is implemented and operational controls pertaining to the waste, then your organization should be ready to yield the advantages."}]
2c:["$","footer",null,{"className":"mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"flex flex-wrap gap-2","children":[["$","span","0",{"className":"text-xs font-semibold text-gray-600 bg-gray-100 px-2 py-1 rounded","children":"5 steps to Manage Wastes according to ISO 14001 EMS"}]]}]}]
